<h3><strong>15. Audio and podcast marketing</strong></h3>
<p>Nearly <a href="https://www.business2community.com/digital-marketing/numbers-and-facts-you-need-to-know-about-audio-content-in-2021-02398919" target="_blank" rel="noopener">60%</a> of people agree audio is more engaging than other forms of content. Donâ€™t just get eyes on your content, get ears on them too. The emergence of audio across marketing channels in recent years has brought to light the endless audio capabilities businesses now have.</p>
<p>For example, <a href="https://blog.hubspot.com/marketing/marketing-channels" target="_blank" rel="noopener">55%</a> of the U.S. population aged 12 and above listen to podcasts. There is a podcast for just about every <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/niche-markets/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">niche market</a> out there, so see if you can place an ad for your business on a popular, fitting podcast. Or, start your own podcast to <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/brand-community/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">build your brandâ€™s community</a>!</p>
<p>Another way audio has crept into the marketing world is through <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2019/03/19/social-media-for-small-business" target="_blank" rel="noopener">social media</a>. Many platforms now offer ways to foster communities through virtual chat rooms with designated speakers and listeners. For example, <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/twitter-updates-2021/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Twitter introduced Twitter Spaces</a> as well as voice tweets. With Twitter Spaces, folks can listen and chat with others about hot topics. Voice tweets are audio clips followers can playback.</p>
<p>By using these platforms, you can discuss your brand while also connecting with your audience.</p>
<p><strong>Audio marketing tips:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Write scripts.</strong> Thereâ€™s nothing wrong with preplanning what you will say in your audio content. Writing a script or even loose notes ahead of time can save you from slip-ups if your audio content is being recorded live.</li>
<li><strong>Promote your audio clips on other marketing channels.</strong> Whatâ€™s audio content without listeners? Be sure to draw attention to your audio marketing so people know to keep an ear out for it.</li>
<li><strong>Practice makes perfect.</strong> If your audio efforts donâ€™t take off right away, donâ€™t give up! Keep practicing and putting out audio content, as it will take time to build up a loyal listener base.</li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/marketing-channels-twitter-space-example.jpg" alt="marketing channels - screenshot of a twitter space" width="900" height="632" class="aligncenter wp-image-73300 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/marketing-channels-twitter-space-example.jpg 900w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/marketing-channels-twitter-space-example-480x337.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 900px, 100vw" /></p>
