<h3><strong>17. Marketing with website chat</strong></h3>
<p><a href="https://www.inc.com/nicolas-cole/the-power-of-live-chat-5-surprising-statistics-that-show-how-consumers-want-thei.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">92%</a> of customers feel satisfied with their experience after using <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/live-chat-benefits/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">live chat</a>, so donâ€™t miss out on this easy website win this year! <a href="https://localiq.com/products/chat/?&amp;itm_source=localiq&amp;itm_medium=blog&amp;itm_campaign=incontent_links" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Adding live chat</a> can work as a bonus marketing channel because it can make suggestions to customers. For example, your chatbot could promote a new product or offer users an exclusive deal.</p>
<p><strong>Live chat tips:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Provide options. </strong>Be sure your prompts not only include marketing mentions but also have plenty of options for the various needs your web visitors may have.</li>
<li><strong>Personalize your bot. </strong>Adding a bit of personality to your live chat experience will make your customersâ€™ chat more enjoyable.</li>
<li><strong>Run quality checks early on. </strong>Be sure to run tests and check that all of your chatâ€™s responses make sense before a customer gets caught up in a nonsensical chat.</li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/marketing-channels-live-chat-example.png" alt="marketing channels - example of live chat " width="310" height="559" class="aligncenter wp-image-73301 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/marketing-channels-live-chat-example.png 310w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/marketing-channels-live-chat-example-166x300.png 166w" sizes="(max-width: 310px) 100vw, 310px" /></p>
