										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Unless you went to clown college (props to you if you did), you probably struggle to pull off the classic â€œjuggling actâ€ of marketing your business as much as possible.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/cross-channel-marketing-meme.png" alt="cross-channel marketing - meme about a to-do list with everything on it" width="422" height="420" class="aligncenter wp-image-62123 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/cross-channel-marketing-meme.png 422w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/cross-channel-marketing-meme-300x300.png 300w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/cross-channel-marketing-meme-150x150.png 150w" sizes="(max-width: 422px) 100vw, 422px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Marketing your business can sometimes feel like this. </em></p>
<p>However, it doesnâ€™t always have to feel like youâ€™re performing tricks to market your business successfully across the board. Today, Iâ€™m going to show you how you can market your business for maximized success without jumping through hoops. The secret is cross-channel marketing. Now, just hearing that word may raise some questionsâ€”which Iâ€™ll provide the answers to, like:</p>
<p>Letâ€™s jump right in!</p>
<h2>Cross-channel marketing guide table of contents</h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="#cross-channel-definition">What is cross-channel marketing?</a></li>
<li><a href="#difference">The difference between cross-channel and multi-channel marketing</a>.</li>
